  <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>Small Font Blog for small font product insights Worldwide</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Follow small font release notes, case studies, and small font playbooks that guide product teams toward accessible typography and privacy-first operations." />
    <meta name="keywords" content="" />
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://osrsdmmge.online/en/blog/" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/site.css" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/assets/small-font-icon.svg" />
  </head>
  <body class="bg-midnight text-fog antialiased">
    {{ languageAlert | safe }}
    {{ renderHeader(header) }}
        <main class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4 pb-24 pt-12 md:px-8">
      <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center space-y-6">
        <span class="badge">Editorial</span>
        <h1 class="section-title">Small font blog insights for small font teams</h1>
        <p class="text-secondary">Deep dives on small font workflows, accessibility tactics, and privacy-first analytics written for product teams shipping modern UI.</p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3">
          <span class="rounded-full bg-white/10 px-4 py-1 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-secondary">Guides</span>
          <span class="rounded-full bg-white/10 px-4 py-1 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-secondary">Playbooks</span>
          <span class="rounded-full bg-white/10 px-4 py-1 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-secondary">Case Studies</span>
          <span class="rounded-full bg-white/10 px-4 py-1 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-secondary">Accessibility</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mx-auto flex w-full max-w-xl flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row">
          <input type="search" placeholder="Search small font stories" class="w-full rounded-full border border-border/40 bg-black/40 px-4 py-3 text-sm text-white placeholder-white/40 focus:border-accent focus:outline-none" />
          <button type="button" class="btn w-full sm:w-auto">Subscribe</button>
        </div>
      </section>
      <section class="mt-16 space-y-12">
        <div class="grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-2">
          <article class="group panel transition hover:border-accent hover:shadow-glow">
            <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-fog/50">Apr 2, 2025 • Guides</p>
            <h2 class="mt-4 text-xl font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-accent">Adaptive small font patterns</h2>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-secondary">Blueprints for responsive small font typography across watch, phone, and desktop breakpoints, with accessibility baked in from day one.</p>
            <a href="/en/blog/adaptive-small-font.html" class="mt-6 inline-flex items-center text-sm font-semibold text-accent">Read story →</a>
          </article>
          <article class="group panel transition hover:border-accent hover:shadow-glow">
            <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-fog/50">Mar 18, 2025 • Case Study</p>
            <h2 class="mt-4 text-xl font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-accent">Scaling small font localization</h2>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-secondary">How a global fintech translated small font copy into six languages while keeping tone, privacy, and legal copy aligned.</p>
            <a href="/en/blog/scaling-small-font-localization.html" class="mt-6 inline-flex items-center text-sm font-semibold text-accent">Read story →</a>
          </article>
          <article class="group panel transition hover:border-accent hover:shadow-glow">
            <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-fog/50">Mar 5, 2025 • Playbook</p>
            <h2 class="mt-4 text-xl font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-accent">Audit your small font CX</h2>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-secondary">A 30 minute audit checklist that uncovers readability gaps, contrast issues, and trust signals hiding in small font UI moments.</p>
            <a href="/en/blog/audit-small-font-cx.html" class="mt-6 inline-flex items-center text-sm font-semibold text-accent">Read story →</a>
          </article>
        </div>
        <div class="grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-3">
          <article class="panel panel-contrast">
            <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-fog/50">Feb 20, 2025 • Accessibility</p>
            <h2 class="mt-4 text-lg font-semibold text-white">Privacy-first analytics for small font UI</h2>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-secondary">Measure conversion without compromising on privacy by instrumenting first-party, consent-friendly metrics for small font interfaces.</p>
            <a href="/en/blog/privacy-first-small-font-analytics.html" class="mt-6 inline-flex items-center text-sm font-semibold text-accent">Read story →</a>
          </article>
          <article class="panel panel-contrast">
            <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-fog/50">Feb 2, 2025 • Playbook</p>
            <h2 class="mt-4 text-lg font-semibold text-white">Small font onboarding in seven steps</h2>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-secondary">Embed small font thinking into sprint rituals with facilitation tips, prompts, and governance guardrails for product teams.</p>
            <a href="/en/blog/small-font-onboarding-seven-steps.html" class="mt-6 inline-flex items-center text-sm font-semibold text-accent">Read story →</a>
          </article>
          <article class="panel panel-contrast">
            <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-fog/50">Jan 18, 2025 • Guides</p>
            <h2 class="mt-4 text-lg font-semibold text-white">Design tokens for small font systems</h2>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-secondary">Map typography tokens to code using JSON, CSS, and Tailwind bridges so small font decisions ship consistently.</p>
            <a href="/en/blog/small-font-design-tokens.html" class="mt-6 inline-flex items-center text-sm font-semibold text-accent">Read story →</a>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
    {{ renderFooterSecondary(footer) }}
